# How to Submit a Pull Request to Update the Central Index (PROJECTS.md)

Follow these steps to add your project to the central index in **FR-published-codes**.

---

## 1. Fork the Repository

- Visit [FR-published-codes](https://github.com/FR-published-codes/FR-published-codes).
- Click the **“Fork”** button (top-right corner) to create a copy under your account.

---

## 2. Clone Your Fork Locally

- Click **“Code”** and copy the repository URL from your fork.
- In your terminal, run:
  ```
  git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/FR-published-codes.git
  ```
- Replace `YOUR-USERNAME` with your GitHub username.

---

## 3. Create a New Branch

- Change to the repository directory:
  ```
  cd FR-published-codes
  ```
- Create and switch to a new branch:
  ```
  git checkout -b add-my-project
  ```

---

## 4. Edit `PROJECTS.md`

- Open `PROJECTS.md` in your editor.
- Add a new row for your project in the table, following this format:
  ```
  | Project Name | Lead Researcher / Group | Repo Link | Publications | Datasets | Dependencies |
  |--------------|------------------------|-----------|--------------|----------|--------------|
  | YourProject  | Your Name              | [repo](https://github.com/FR-published-codes/yourproject) | [Paper](https://doi.org/...) | [Dataset](https://...) | [requirements.txt](...) |
  ```
- Save your changes.

---

## 5. Commit and Push Your Changes

- Stage and commit your changes:
  ```
  git add PROJECTS.md
  git commit -m "Add my project to central index"
  ```
- Push your branch to your fork:
  ```
  git push origin add-my-project
  ```

---

## 6. Create a Pull Request

- Go to your fork on GitHub.
- Click **“Compare & pull request”** for the branch you just pushed.
- Fill out the PR form (title, description), explaining your addition.
- Submit the pull request.

---

## 7. Wait for Review and Merge

- Repository admins will review your submission.
- They may request changes or merge your pull request.

---

## Alternative: Edit Directly on GitHub

- You can also edit `PROJECTS.md` using GitHub's web interface on your fork.
- After editing, GitHub will prompt you to create a pull request.

---

For more details, see [CONTRIBUTING.md](../CONTRIBUTING.md).
